Thank the Lord! Bishop Jakes’ for your life and the life that your ministry gives to each of us. It has been my highest joy to serve in your shadow. Others go “up” but you insist on carrying others up with you. May your 66 years be followed by many more years of abundant blessings. May you continue to turn good into great. Happy Birthday and much love from Al and Cynthia James.

Happy Juneteenth! 
“ Please note this is my personal view”
Anything that sparks conversation about past and current injustices afflicted on Black Communities and which promotes the accurate telling of our history is of utmost importance.  However, it should be emphasized that the Emancipation Proclamation was not intended nor did it in fact free the slaves. It was a strategy issued on behalf of the Union . It provided along with other matters that the Union army was no longer required to return to slavery those slaves who made it to Union lines. By the time the word reached Galveston , Tx the war between Union and Confederate armies had ended.  Until the 13 th Amendment was signed 6 months after Juneteenth, Blacks still were not declared free citizens. I presume  they were considered to be “ Contraband “ like others who escaped to Union lines. So we commemorate knowing that 2 years priors a way had been instituted that did not free all slaves but which  initiated a serious blow against the constant supplying of fighting men to Confederate armies.The Struggle Continues.
